request.description:
PUBLIC diagnostic endpoint requiring no authentication. Returns raw inventory counts (total, active true/false/undefined), a sample of the 20 most recent items, up to 5 plants, and current user context if a valid bearer token is present. Intended to diagnose why items are not showing. No side effects.

**Auth:** Public (no auth)

**Example response (200):**
```json
{
  "ok": true,
  "data": {
    "db": {
      "totalItems": 128,
      "activeTrue": 120,
      "activeFalse": 3,
      "activeUndefined": 5
    },
    "currentUser": {
      "id": "665f0a1b2c3d4e5f60718293",
      "email": "operator@sanmati.com",
      "hasWildcard": false,
      "permCount": 12
    },
    "plants": [
      {
        "id": "665f0a1b2c3d4e5f6071aaaa",
        "name": "Sanmati Plant 1",
        "code": "P1"
      }
    ],
    "sample": [
      {
        "_id": "665f0a1b2c3d4e5f60718200",
        "sku": "FILM-BOPP-20",
        "name": "BOPP Film 20 micron",
        "type": "raw",
        "onHand": 1500,
        "active": true
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

Authenticates a user and issues an access token + refresh token. Body may optionally be base64-encoded (isEncoded=true). Rejects if user not found, not active, or password invalid. Side effects: creates a RefreshToken record and updates lastLoginAt.

**Auth:** Public (no auth)

**Example response (200):**
```json
{
  "ok": true,
  "data": {
    "accessToken": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.<payload>.<sig>",
    "refreshToken": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.<payload>.<sig>",
    "user": {
      "id": "66f0a123b4c5d6e7f8012345",
      "name": "System Admin",
      "email": "admin@example.com",
      "employeeCode": "ADMIN"
    }
  }
}
```

Verifies the refresh token JWT and rotates it with reuse detection: if the token hash is missing or already revoked, the whole token family is revoked (reuse detection). On success the old token is revoked and a new access/refresh pair is issued. Error codes: E_REFRESH, E_REFRESH_REUSE, E_REFRESH_REVOKED, E_REFRESH_EXPIRED.

**Auth:** Public (no auth)

**Example response (200):**
```json
{
  "ok": true,
  "data": {
    "accessToken": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.<new>.<sig>",
    "refreshToken": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.<new>.<sig>"
  }
}
```

Revokes the supplied refresh token (sets revokedAt on the matching record). Does not affect other sessions.

**Auth:** JWT Bearer

**Example response (200):**
```json
{
  "ok": true,
  "data": {
    "success": true
  }
}
```

Revokes all active refresh tokens for the authenticated user and increments tokenVersion (invalidating all existing access tokens once the Redis cache TTL expires). Uses req.user from the bearer token; no body needed.

**Auth:** JWT Bearer

**Example response (200):**
```json
{
  "ok": true,
  "data": {
    "success": true
  }
}
```

