Fully-dynamic telemetry ingestion. Machine identified by iotAuth (URL :code, body machineId, or X-Machine-Code header) and authenticated via X-API-Key. Accepts a single event object, an array of events, or a wrapped batch ({ events: [...] }) — 1 to 500 events. Known fields become indexed columns; aliases are mapped (production->unitsProduced, reject->rejects, operator->operatorCode, alarm->alarmCode, order_id->orderId); everything else (plus a provided metrics object) lands in metrics. state is validated against running|idle|maintenance|down|offline. Side effects: bulk-inserts MachineData, enqueues a BullMQ 'process-event' job per state_change/alarm/cycle_end/counter event, and emits Socket.IO live events to the plant/machine room. Returns HTTP 202.

